<recipe>
    <name>Peanut Sauce (NAAM SA-TE)</name>
    <indexCharacter>P</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>8</servings>
    <instructions>MAKES 1 1/2 CUPS 

HEAT 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in a saucepan and fry the garlic, Asian shallots and lemongrass for a minute. Add the Thai curry powder arid stir until fragrant. 

ADD the tamarind puree, chilli paste, peanuts and palm sugar and bring slowly to a boil. Add enough coconut milk to make a spoonable sauce and simmer for 2 minutes. Season with salt to taste.</instructions>
